info.author: Mark Muetzelfeldt
info.description:
This is a django application that provides a hierarchical navigation system.
It takes over the URL naming for the resources that it is charge of, but should
otherwise play nicely with existing projects. It defaults to using
django.contrib.flatpages for the content, but can be linked to any other content.
It can provide tight integration with javascript (jquery), and css for the dropdown
menu, and allows you to set colours/pictures based on nav_item through the django
admin interface.

It currently requires the latest development version of Django (from subversion) and
PIL (Python Image Library). It should work with Django 1.2 when that is released.
info.name: django-navtree
info.summary: Django application for adding hierarchical navigation to projects
info.html_description:
This is a django application that provides a hierarchical navigation system. It takes over the URL naming for the resources that it is charge of, but should otherwise play nicely with existing projects. It defaults to using django.contrib.flatpages for the content, but can be linked to any other content. It can provide tight integration with javascript (jquery), and css for the dropdown menu, and allows you to set colours/pictures based on nav_item through the django admin interface.

It currently requires the latest development version of Django (from subversion) and PIL (Python Image Library). It should work with Django 1.2 when that is released.
